## Step 1 – Create Your GitHub Account (Takes 2–3 Minutes)

1. Open browser → go to https://github.com
2. Click big green **Sign up** button
3. Enter email (Gmail recommended)
4. Create strong password
5. Pick username — make it professional and memorable  
   Good examples: codewithyou, dev-yourinitials, yourname-tech, pythonlover2026  
   Avoid: random numbers, offensive words, too long
6. Solve captcha → verify email → account created!

Pro tip: Use this same username on LinkedIn, Twitter/X, LeetCode, resume — brand consistency helps.

## Step 2 – Build an Attractive Profile README (Your Digital Front Door)

This is the page everyone sees first when they visit your profile. Make it shine!

1. On GitHub homepage → click green **+** icon → **New repository**
2. Repository name → **exactly** your username (e.g. if username is "dev-abc" then repo name = "dev-abc")
3. Check the box **Add a README file**
4. Click green **Create repository**
5. On the new repo page → click pencil icon ✏️ on README.md to edit

