## Step 3 – Your Very First Commit (Start the Green Magic TODAY)

Goal: Make your contribution graph show green squares — recruiters notice streaks!

1. From homepage → **+** → New repository
2. Name it something simple: hello-github, my-journey, first-steps-2026
3. Make it Public + check **Add a README file** → Create repository
4. On repo page → click pencil ✏️ on README.md
5. Type anything:  
   "My GitHub journey started today — March 2026!  
   Goal: learn, build, contribute, land internship."
6. Scroll down → green **Commit changes** button → Commit!

Do **one tiny commit every single day** — edit README, add a note, fix typo.  
Even 1 line counts. Graph fills fast.

