## Step 4 – Build Projects (The Heart of Your Profile – Make 5–10+)

Projects are what recruiters actually look at.

Start super simple → scale up:

Beginner level (0–3 months):
- Static personal webpage (HTML + CSS)
- Responsive portfolio site
- To-do list app (JavaScript)
- Number guessing game (Python)
- Rock-paper-scissors game
- Basic calculator

Intermediate (3–6 months):
- Weather app using free API
- Quiz app with score
- Blog site (HTML/CSS/JS)
- Simple CRUD app (local storage)
- Mini e-commerce page mockup

Advanced:
- Full-stack todo with backend (Node/Express or Flask)
- Chatbot basics
- Data visualization dashboard
- ML model demo (push from Colab)

For EVERY project:
1. New repository → good name (e.g. todo-app-js, weather-fetcher)
2. Add code files
3. Create killer README.md:  
   - Project title & screenshot  
   - Live demo link (GitHub Pages)  
   - How to run/install  
   - Tech used  
   - What I learned/challenges  
   - Future improvements
4. Commit often (good messages: "Added UI", "Fixed bug in fetch")
5. Pin 4–6 best projects on your profile (profile settings → pin)

