## Step 5 – Open Source Contributions (The Biggest Game-Changer)

Even total beginners can contribute!

1. Go to GitHub search → type: "good first issue" + your skill  
   Example: "good first issue javascript" or "good first issue python beginner"
2. Great starter repos:  
   - first-contributions (easiest ever)  
   - freeCodeCamp  
   - awesome lists (add resources)  
   - beginner-friendly projects tagged "good first issue"

Contribution flow:
- Find issue → read it
- Click **Fork** (top right)
- Edit file online (or clone locally later)
- Make small fix: typo, add name to contributors.md, better comment, small feature
- Commit with clear message
- Go to your fork → **Pull requests** → **New pull request**
- Submit → wait (many get merged quickly)

One merged PR = massive credibility boost. Aim for 3–5 in first 6 months.

